title: 'The Mickey Mouse Club' turns 60: Where are they now?
text: Blogs 'The Mickey Mouse Club' turns 60: Where are they now? On Oct. 3, 1955 the original 'Mickey Mouse Club' premiered, which later spawned two revivals, 'The New Mickey Mouse Club' and 'The All-New Mickey Mouse Club.' See which of your favorite Mouseketeers grew up to be megastars â€¦ Photo: Getty Images./ Published: 10/3/2015 9:00:00 Britney Spears Britney Spears auditioned for "Mickey Mouse Club" when she was eight years old, but was rejected for being too young. She went on to appear on Broadway and the talent search show "Star Search." In 1992, she finally landed the role on "Mickey Mouse Club" and starred on it until it was canceled in 1994. The exposure helped her to get signed to a record label and her career as a pop star skyrocketed through the 1990s and early 2000s. Despite some personal struggles Britney faced in 2007, she is still on top of her game and is currently performing in a residency show in Las Vegas. 1 of 6
